content: Great single player monster-taming RPG, what I was looking for. I LOVE that each monster is a unique character and really wish more in the subgenre did this. Has a lot of loose ends plot-wise I'd like to see resolved and a few types of monsters dont join you (Pancho, Will O Wisp, "man", and bird) could really use a sequel or update! I'd pay more money! >_<

Discount Legend of the Tetrarchs. Nonetheless, it was a good game with 25+ characters you can use to create your party, plus different classes. Storyline is subtly dark, with a generic main antagonist, but with some underlying motives if you explore. All in all a good game.
Great game in all respects just wish the ending was better

Classic Kemco game. A good return of the (semi) silent protagonist of unknown origin. The only critic is the dialog style change which was a bit disorienting for me. But it was ok once you get used to it.

Great fantasy monster catching JRPG! Loved the creatures, character classes, and skill system. Nice story too. Also liked not having to heal outside of battle & strengthening equipment instead of buying new ones often.

I love it this game absolutely loved it, I need more story and alternate story like a more chapter comes the future, I'm really addicted to this game in Monster Viator in 24 hours all monster and beat the game I wish monster been collected take new side story I'll give 10/10 rate, I really like dragon being cute and cool dude.
Very frustrated with the game. Instruction are not very clear & help menu is useless
I bought this game it keep cutting off while am playing it.fix it or refund me.

I'm about 15 hours into the game and I'm loving it. No issues or errors. Game runs great on my LG V20 and Razer 2. Loveable characters, good storyline, ok controls. Could do without the 10 dollar price tag, then the really unessesary over priced iap "extra" features. It should be 10 bucks for the game, no iap. All extras should be unlockable by beating the game.
I change my review to 5 star, seem 2x dmg is not bugged, I'm wrong bz I use weak element monster to fight. Cheer

Your on the right track, I love Rpg's and turned based games. But HATE 1st person point of view. The story is interesting enough and would have been alot better if It was in 3rd person perspective. I could actually see the characters and monster move like the other games you've created. It Ethier a hit or miss ! I wish it was set up like a band of monsters. I would have paid more to have a game like that.
seems like a good kemco rpg so far, hit point has done a pretty decent job taking eliments for their previous work that worked so well to make this game quite fun to play.
No support for the many displays that have a notch/display cutout.
replyContent:
Thank you for your sincere feedback! Unfortunately, this game currently does not support notch, however, we 
will use your feedback to improve future game experience!
